        <caption>
          <p>The ratio of total genes and HGT events per phylum and the ratio of HGT events which occurred between and within taxa. (<bold>A</bold>) The relative frequency of prokaryotic genomesâ total genes and HGT-related genes was visualized at the phylum level. More HGT-related genes were detected as the total number of genes in the phylum was larger. (<bold>B</bold>) The <italic toggle="yes">x</italic>-axis shows the ratio of the HGT-related genes and the <italic toggle="yes">y</italic>-axis shows the taxonomy of the animal kingdom, from the genus level to the phylum level. The yellow peaks show the ratio of HGT events between different taxa, and the blue peaks show the ratio of those that occurred within the same taxonomy. Both peaks were denser as the taxonomy levels were higher, meaning more genes were transferred between closely related organisms.</p>
